metadata.name: OpenProject Cybersecurity Dataset
metadata.description: Labeled cybersecurity dataset from a live OpenProject instance. Normal and attack traffic across 7 MITRE ATT&CK techniques with Caddy/Rails telemetry merged by trace ID.

application.name: OpenProject 14.x
application.stack: Ruby on Rails + PostgreSQL + Memcached + Caddy reverse proxy

observability.labeling: Docker Compose label overlays (event.label, attack.technique, attack.tactic)

T1078.name: Valid Accounts
T1078.description: Credential stuffing and brute force login attempts using common username/password combinations

T1083.name: File and Directory Discovery
T1083.description: Enumeration of application file structure, API endpoints, and directory listings

T1071.001.name: Application Layer Protocol: Web
T1071.001.description: C2-style periodic HTTP beaconing with encoded payloads to application endpoints

T1190.name: Exploit Public-Facing Application
T1190.description: SQL injection, XSS, path traversal, and code injection payloads in HTTP parameters

T1498.002.name: Reflection Amplification DDoS
T1498.002.description: High-volume HTTP flood targeting search and API endpoints to cause denial of service

T1548.name: Abuse Elevation Control Mechanism
T1548.description: Unauthorized access attempts to admin panels, user management, and privileged API endpoints

T1595.002.name: Active Scanning: Vulnerability Scanning
T1595.002.description: Probing for sensitive files (.env, .git, wp-admin), known CVEs, and server misconfigurations

trace_id.description: Distributed trace ID linking proxy and app logs for the same HTTP request

attack_technique.description: MITRE ATT&CK technique ID (malicious events only)

attack_tactic.description: MITRE ATT&CK tactic category (malicious events only)

http_uri.description: Request URI path with query parameters
